caption: This location is absolutely outstanding. I'll return with my relatives. It has a cool atmosphere.
Don't worry if it's busy, it is worth the wait. The service here is great. It has a nice interior. Menu is like a cafe in Indianapolis I loved.

Great customer service. Mediocre food for more upscale prices. Ordered an omlette it was super thick egg that looked as though it was premade and filled with the topings. Wish the salmon Benedict had more Benedict. Everything was ok. Just heard people rave  about the place.  Customer service was great especially during these times.  Maybe we should've stuck to the baked goods.
Definitely going to come back again.

My "Roast Beef" sandwich was really a very small piece of grilled meat, probably Flank Steak. It was just okay, and definitely not what I was expecting. Rising Roll's Roast Beef is truly Roast Beef and much better.
The pancakes were dry. Sticking to the French toast.

Well polished and well-run establishment. Great variety of sandwiches, soups, and salads. The prices are maybe a bit high for what you get but the quality is hard to beat -- I might go so far as to say this is the best sandwich-centric place in the area
Food is amazing!

Always a good lunch/breakfast option. The sweet potato buscuit is a good addition to your order. The wait staff could do a better job at letting guests know how service works. My guest didn't know that coffee orders would not be brought to the table.
Good soups and sandwiches, their Reuben has a good heat to it. Coffee is alright, not exceptional but much better than any chain place. Overall a good place to grab lunch downtown
Love the Highland Bakery Downtown.   The staff great and always helpful and friendly. The food s first class with soup, salads and sandwiches. I am so glad they are in downtown Atlanta.
Very nice people and service. Good food.
Amazing breakfast and very spacious seating area.
French toast is delicious
Great French toast.  Too rich to eat often, but damn good.
Love this bakery! They have the BEST shakes and smoothies and a ton of flavours to choose from. The service is pretty good and the bathrooms are really nice and well kept
French toast and Hazelnut cappuccino! Love it!! :)
I ordered the first sandwich called ultimate something, forgive me couldn't remember the name, but it's taste great! The environment is also good. Would recommend to sit in.
Food not good (even the desserts) & pricey. Nonchalant customer service from the workers.
Good coffee good food. Sweet potato biscuit is awesome.
Great downtown location of this wonderful bakery. Was happy to see they had the curried chicken salad sandwich on the menu at this location as well.

The soups and sandwiches are good, but the coffees are really bitter and the hot chocolate as a fruity/funky taste to it. Be careful when asking for a pastry or brownie to be warmed up - I've burned my mouth on a few because they microwave it for too long.
Amazing service and food; highly recommended during the weekdays in downtown Atlanta
You'll have to pay to park, and parking is hard to find. The food is mediocre and a bit overpriced too. The inside is open and clean, and the staff is friendly. It's an ok place to eat downtown.
Great place to get a quick bite! good prices for good food!

With no shortage of coffee shops in Downtown, I was happy to see Highland Bakery open up to offer something new to the mix. I ordered an iced coffee and brownie and asked for the brownie to be heated. I was not impressed. I offer my suggestions to the owner and/or manager. 1) Do not heat baked goods in a microwave for 30 seconds. Get a toaster oven. 2) If a customer chooses a baked good for inside dining, offer it to them on a plate... not a bag. 3) If you're not willing to add sweetener or milk to a coffee, leave room for it when the guests asks. 4) Don't give guests a number to be seated for coffee and then yell out "iced coffee" at the counter and expect the customer to fetch it. 5) Get WiFi.
Service good, but sandwich was pretty weak
My mom works here. I get free food. Amazing helpers. Amazing service
Great food and plenty of pastries to grab for tomorrow's breakfast.
Food good. Service  always a bit shoddy
Aesthetically pleasing. Food wasnt bad.
Food is good but a bit pricey. Coffee is scalding hot, so I would recommend waiting at least 5 minutes before drinking it. Atmosphere is really nice.
I took Thai peanut salad and was disappointed to see half of my salad leaves to be yellow (spoiled). My americano tasted as they were using the same coffee for several cups. Upset.
Great service with good portions of food. The Italian veggie sandwich with the white-bean chili was great. The roast beef is a classic that can't go wrong. It was also good.

Wow! My co-worker and I were running an errand on our lunch break when she pointed this place out. I love decor. I wasn't going to have anything but she insisted. Glad to say I did. I loved it. I'm making plans to bring my wife/foodie as soon as possible.
I like their coffee!
Good comfort food
the tomato bisque is lit, wish they had more outlets, if they did I would study here more often

I visited this location for the first time today (11/12/18). My Mango Tango smoothy was tasty and made quickly. It's a convenient location being in the same building as all of my professor's offices. The staff was neither friendly nor unfriendly towards me, but they did seem very unhappy to be there. They were certainly ready to go home when I ordered my smoothy at 4pm.  I wonder if that is due to the quantity and volume of the country music that was playing. Typically most cafes have easy listening music playing at a reasonable volume, not this establishment. During the 30 minutes I was here the lineup consisted exclusively of country music being blasted at a level that would make a bar in southern Georgia proud. (Loud enough to hear through my headphones.)  Hopefully if you visit this location you're planning on a quick in and out. Otherwise you'll probably be as ready to leave as the employees by the time your coffee cools enough to drink.
Excellent. Would definitely recommend.

Convenient location. Serviceable coffee. However, their baked goods need to actually be baked. I ordered a ham and cheese croissant, which was great initially. However, I got halfway through and realized the dough was uncooked with raw sections. I couldn't finish it.
The food is always reliably average.

Definitely won't be going back to this location. The Highland Bakery-Decatur is a completely different world with different quality standards. I made a pickup order (arrived as soon as the email told me) and my Fried Chicken Biscuit was barely fried, sad, and soggy. The box my food came in was also dirty (see photo). I didn't order fruit or lip-gloss with my meal so no explanation for the stains. Customer service was mediocre and they weren't even busy. Don't waste your money.

I ordered a crab burger and got a lump of crab meat in a regular wheat slice of bread.  It is advertised as being on a Kaiser bun.  The customer service is mediocre.  I had to get the cashier, repeat myself several times to place my order, and then received the sandwich.  Also I observed that another customer had the wrong order.  She let them know it was wrong and when she received it, it was still wrong.  I will make sure I just walk right by next time.

Great place for breakfast. I stop here whenever I have time in the morning and get a Shot in the dark and a turkey sausage egg and cheese biscuit. I’ve lived in GA for a while, so believe me when I say this is a top10 biscuit! I would recommend this place to anyone who works in the area
Best shrimp and grits I've had in a long time and their French toast was amazing!!!

Not impressed with staff. Left us standing with half the drinks. Had to ask for what I paid for, and had to go back and ask for rest of food. Expensive for  what we got. Don't think it will be a second stop for us.

I LOVE Highland Bakery. I believe this might actually be the only one I’ve been to. The Soup of the Day is always delicious (which you MUST get because, no matter what it is, it comes with a piece of bread with melted cheese and peppers on top). The sandwiches are out of this world! I just wish it was open on the weekends!
Nice seating indoor or outdoor. Menu was ok but fresh selection seemed limited. Maybe it was because GSU was out of session.

It may share the "Highland Bakery" name, but don't be fooled when trying to use any Highland Bakery gift cards. I attempted to use a gift card from another location and I was told "They are different systems so it won't work."  Extremely disappointed.
A tad expensive but nonetheless delicious.
The coffee here is terrible, if you want a good cup go a block away to Ebriks.  The only reason this place gets 3 stars is because their food is decent.
the original location in Inman park is so much better. they left food out of my order, everything was cold and gross, and the staff wasn't very friendly

Really enjoyed the downtown location. Highland Bakery did an impressive job of bringing the quality of their food and service to this smaller outpost. Despite the size, I really appreciated the space. It was comfortable and open, and the kind of place where you can camp out and work or have an informal work meeting.
Great atmosphere
So delicious. I wish they had fries though.

I don't think the people working here enjoy it very much, and that comes across in their passive aggressiveness. I ordered a mocha within 30 minutes of them closing, and it was like I'd asked a teenager to clean her room. The food feels like it may be premade off-site and warmed here. It's got the feel of an airport restaurant.
Cozy atmosphere and delicious food!
A nice pit stop before class.
Parking a pain
Great food, reasonable prices, and excellent customer service! 👌

The food is good (not amazing, but no complaints). This is a fantastic alternative study spot to Starbucks, which is always crowded. Besides the lunch time rush, the Highland Bakery is usually pretty quiet, and the music is great (90's rock/at). Good  cheap coffee too!
not impressed
The sweet potato biscuits are stupendous!

Do not order take out! They will cheat you! Crab Cake Benedict is just not the same with out the Holindase! And can't find a hint of a lump of crab.The potatoes were not fully cooked. The reviews were so good,  I'm very disappointed. The service was good. I'm pleased to be able to say that.

Mixed emotions. The service was great, very friendly people. People are constantly working to keep place clean.  Patrons look comfortable and relaxed. Coffee was delicious.  Views were great.  I had the Thai peanut salad with tofu and it was not good. It was this weird warm noodle peanut glob on top of some lettuce.  No dressing.  It just didn't go well.  I'd return for something to give it another try.
Delicious sandwiches!
Ultimate chicken sandwich!!!!!!!!!!!!
The breakfast BLT is amazing.

Quick, excellent service and lots of choices both healthy and indulgent. Tons of seating. Not exactly cozy, though, and at lunch time the lines are long. Its one of my favorite spots downtown to get takeout.
A bit overpriced for the portions, but convenient for Park Place. A nice place to meet for coffee.
Very fresh, tasty food with healthy options. It's kind of pricey, but they also have good coffee, pastries, and spacious seating.

Spacious. Great place to study while sipping on a cup of coffee. I ordered the highland breakfast with a side of potatoes and my friend ordered the ricotta pancakes. The pancakes we're soft and tasteful. So was the egg scramble in my dish. But the potatoes were burnt and inedible. Other than that it was a great experience and good crowd. Will definitely go back to try other stuff.
Upscale trendy college cafe restaurant.

I love the atmosphere, food and service. This place is good for a sit down meal or a grab and go. It's also s good place to do work as long as you don't need a laptop or your laptop has an awesome battery (there are only 2 plugs in the whole restaurant). The prices are also pretty reasonable. Check it out of you can!
Always love this place. Great breakfast and lunch options with delicious pastries
i had the chicken sandwich which was awesome!

THE SERVICE GIVEN BY THE SMALL STAFF IS TERRIFIC!! COULDN'T BE BETTER...the food is great served quickly with a smile!!(even the busser team was handling customers with the BEST attitudes...)LOVE THIS PLACE!! RECOMMEND ALL OF ATLANTA TO, stop in for a great dinning experience!!!
